<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,310,947,973]" box="[189,310,947,973]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,947,973]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,947,973]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,996,1096]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Antenna entirely black. Femora and tibia black except for knees and tips. Hind tibia with long black dorsal bristles at least twice as long as width of tibia, ventrally with a row of black bristles a little longer than width of tibia.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,324,1138,1164]" box="[189,324,1138,1164]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1138,1164]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1138,1164]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1186,1250]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The species is named after the 
<typeStatus box="[558,609,1187,1213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
locality, the island of 
<collectingRegion box="[875,916,1186,1212]" country="Cape Verde" name="Sal" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Sal</collectingRegion>
. The name 
<collectingRegion box="[1054,1091,1186,1212]" country="Cape Verde" name="Sal" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Sal</collectingRegion>
refers to the salt that was found on the island and also alludes to the saline conditions in which the species was found (
<figureCitation box="[1277,1349,1223,1250]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1015,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,1015,1922]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 6. View of the sebkha to the northwest of Santa Maria (Sal), where Crossopalpus salensis sp. nov. was recorded." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3236107/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
