<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,303,403,429]" box="[189,303,403,429]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,403,429]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,403,429]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1398,450,547]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
The new species does not belong to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[657,944,450,476]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenescens">
<emphasis box="[657,944,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Crossopalpus aenescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Collin J. E." box="[1190,1348,450,477]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="385 - 420" refId="ref6393" refString="Collin J. E. 1960. Some Empididae from Palestine. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 2: 385 - 420. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222935908650872" type="journal article" year="1960">Collin (1960)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith K. G. V." box="[189,348,485,512]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6677" refString="Smith K. G. V. 1967. Afrikanische Empididae (Dipt.). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A 179: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1967">Smith (1967)</bibRefCitation>
, since the right surstylus is a single lobe, while in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[985,1104,486,511]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenescens">
<emphasis box="[985,1104,486,511]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">aenescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group the right surstylus is composed of at least two or three lobes (
<figureCitation box="[691,761,520,546]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[206,1371,1394,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[189,1399,1361,1883]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 8. Crossopalpus complicatus sp. nov., male holotype, terminalia (leg. P. Grootaert and I. Van de Velde, RBINS). A. Right surstyli. B. Lateral view of right epandrial lamella. C. Dorsal view of epandrium, with detail of left surstyli. D. Tip of right surstylus from inside. Scales: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3236111/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1398,585,647]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">It is not clear whether the long bristles on the scutum represent the dorsocentrals and the acrostichal bristles or other bristles, since their position does not correspond exactly to the usual position.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
